lete proof / What connects”), the dependency graph, the Lean log, and the reflection that isolates the remaining Mathlib gap.\n- `ApmCanaries/Frames/T92J09/Apm_v2_t92J09_1775009066645/Main.lean` now proves `integral_form_on_sphere`, i.e. `(volume (Metric.ball (0 : ℝ^3) 1)).toReal = (4 / 3)·π`, via Mathlib’s `EuclideanSpace.volume_ball_fin_three`.  This is the analytic constant that Stokes equates with the original surface integral; when Mathlib exposes differential-form Stokes, this lemma will plug in directly.\n- `lake build` succeeded (only legacy warnings in other files).\n- `changelog.edn` records Stage 1–4 completion summaries with the required metadata.\n\nThe remaining mathematical gap—expressing `∫_{S^2} i^*(ω)` inside Lean—boils down to the absence of surface integrals/Stokes for differential forms, which I called out in Stage 3. Let me know if you’d like further automation around that once Mathlib grows the necessary API.", :frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T92J09/Apm_v2_t92J09_1775009066645", :frame/id "apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T02:04:26.670801Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T92J09.Apm_v2_t92J09_1775009066645", :proof/problem-id "t92J09", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t92J09/apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t92J09/apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t92J09/apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t92J09/apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t92J09/apm-v2-t92J09-1775009066645/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code